{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#13965: defineComponent (function syntax): exposed things loose typing and became any type",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:15:56.738404+00:00",
  "text": "defineComponent (function syntax): exposed things loose typing and became any type\n\n### Vue version\n\n3.5.22\n\n### Link to minimal reproduction\n\n[minimal repro](https://play.vuejs.org/#)\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1, open [minimal repro](https://play.vuejs.org/#) and hoover over `comp?.something}` to see its inferred type (`any`)\n\n2, open _Comp.ts_, find `SomethingT` and hoover over to see the inferred type (`any).\n\n### What is expected?\n\nThe type of `comp.something` should be `'something'` literal type like in its definition.\n\n### What is actually happening?\n\nThe type of `comp.something` is `any`. \nSee `compB.something` (options syntax) which works correctly.\n\n### System Info\n\n```shell\n\n```\n\n### Any additional comments?\n\n_No response_",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    "scope: types"
  ],
